  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nAs title\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nOtherwise, people have to fall back to using `raw_call`, whose intent is less clear.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nAdd a `gas=` kwarg to `send()` which sets the gas stipend. This is also useful for applications which may want to use non-hardcoded gas to avoid issues like those around the constantinople hard fork.\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nNo known issues\r\n\r\n## References\r\n- https://medium.com/chainsecurity/constantinople-enables-new-reentrancy-attack-ace4088297d9\r\n- https://hackmd.io/@axic/solidity-summit-unrestricted-transfer\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
